    "description": "The strategy is a yearly rebalanced value anomaly portfolio that seeks to harvest the cross sectional premium associated with low price to earnings ratios. Each rebalance it builds a US equity universe from stocks with fundamental data and price above 5 dollars, then intentionally tilts into the least liquid segment by selecting the 200 lowest dollar volume names, and finally ranks that set by trailing P E, investing in the 10 stocks with the lowest positive P E ratios. The intended edge is a co",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a yearly rebalanced value anomaly portfolio that seeks to harvest the cross sectional premium associated with low price to earnings ratios. Each rebalance it builds a US equity universe from stocks with fundamental data and price above 5 dollars, then intentionally tilts into the least liquid segment by selecting the 200 lowest dollar volume names, and finally ranks that set by trailing P E, investing in the 10 stocks with the lowest positive P E ratios. The intended edge is a combination of value and liquidity premia, targeting securities that are inexpensive on earnings and potentially under owned or less efficiently priced.\n\nPortfolio construction is long only and equal weighted at 10 percent per name, with full investment and no explicit leverage or volatility targeting. Rebalances occur once per year at the start of the year using fundamental inputs and recent dollar volume; positions are reset to equal weights at each rebalance, implicitly exiting names that fall out of the selection and entering newly qualified names. Aside from diversification across 10 names and the price floor, there are no explicit risk controls such as sector caps, drawdown limits, stop losses, or turnover constraints.",
